problem link : https://leetcode.com/problems/fibonacci-number/description/

Intuition
The fibonacci sequence follows the recurrence relation:

fib(0) = 0
fib(1) = 1
fib(n) = fib(n-1) + fib(n-2) for n > 1

i use recursion to directly implement the recurrence.

the base case handles the smallest fibonacci numbers (0 and 1) for any other value of n , i recursively compute the previous two fibonacci numbers and return their sum.

Approach
if n is 0 , return 0
if n = 1, return 1
recursively compute fib(n-1) and fib(n-2)
return the sum of two values.

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(2^n) each recursive call generates two additional recursive calls, causing many subproblems to be computed repeatedly.

Space complexity:
O(n)
the maximum depth of the recursion stack is n

Code
class Solution:
    def fib(self, n: int) -> int:
        if n == 0:
            return 0
        if n == 1:
            return 1
        ans1 = self.fib(n-1)
        ans2 = self.fib(n-2)
        
        return ans1 + ans2
